data.text: @NighthawkATC Hope it went well. And the next day or so goes well for you also!

24 hours, still good, arm sore if I touch it. Blood sugars were a little lower than normal throughout the morning but only by like 20 to 30 points, so could be vaccine related, could just be bc it wanted to.
17 hours , still feeling good, arm is a little less sore. Blood sugars are staying good as well.

8 hours, still just a sore upper arm if I move it or hit it on something. Blood sugars are looking normal as well (I am on the medtronic 670g, so that may help also with that and a normal immune response showing in my numbers)

5 hours in, sore upper arm like typical vaccine. Blood sugars still looking decent/normal for type 1. Trying to hydrate more than normal just as a preventative measure, added an extra @drinkdripdrop in tonight. Feeling good so far.
@KsutterATC Good to know! My first dose is tomorrow at 2. Been wondering about side effects!

-2.5 hours in, only thing I notice so far is some injection site and upper arm soreness, no diff than any other injection I've ever received. For my diabetic friends, my blood sugars are running normal so far also (I tend to run low when sick so we'll see if I notice any of that)
